==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sowens
<hw>Sow"ens</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Scottish;
cf. AS. <ets>se⟦aacute⟧w</ets> juice, glue, paste.]</ety> <def>A
nutritious article of food, much used in Scotland, made from the husk of
the oat by a process not unlike that by which common starch is made; --
called <altname>flummery</altname> in England.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>sowans</asp>, and <asp>sowins</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sower</ent>⟦br⟧
